				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The US NES adapter (120VAC-&gt;1.3A@9VAC) should be just fine. I remember people mentioning they've done whole-brain swaps of PAL and NTSC NESes (swapping crystal, PPU, CPU, and CIC) and had it work fine, so the adapter should be completely compatible too.<br /><br />In any case, if it asks for 9VAC at 850mA, then any power supply rated for 9VAC at roughly that amount of current will be fine.<br /><br />(Regarding the vizio TV thing: I was kinda surprised when I discovered that my Acer LCD computer monitors support 240p/60 and 288p/50. In fact, the latter is the only 50Hz mode it can parse.)</div>

