						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">neshiggins wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The US power supply should be fine, as has been said, the NES just needs 9V.  I live in the UK but have a US NTSC NES (technically a US NES mainboard in the old case - I wanted to play games at full 60Hz, can't imagine wanting to go the other way!), and the power supply I had for my old UK PAL NES works absolutely fine with it.<br /><br />I'd heard Vizio TVs are pretty handy when it comes to PAL/NTSC support, they're decent for the price.</div><br /><br />My US Power Supply won't fit my PAL NES, the size is a little small. I have the &quot;NES&quot; version made by Mattel. Yes the output is correct: AC9v 1.3A and if I modded it would run fine, but I wound up ordering an UK power supply instead.<br /><br />As far as why I wanted one is that PAL games run to fast on NTSC console, and there are a handful (not many) that are exclusive, but buying a PAL NES is certainly not for everyone and not for most games as they are NTSC. Offhand I can name only two, Smurfs and Mario Bros Classic lol<br /><br />Yes I recommend the Vizio for anyone who wants both NTSC/PAL compatibility.</div>

